description: deed +‎ -less; obsolete sense is from earlier dadless, probably from Old Norse dáðlauss (“without virtue, incapable, lacking in courage and drive, despicable, cowardly”). Cognate with Danish dådløs (“non-heroic”), Swedish dådlös (“listless, shiftless”).

adjectives.description: deedless (comparative more deedless, superlative most deedless)

entries.meaning: (of real property) Of real property whose owners' claim is not evidence by formal record of ownership,  such as a deed.
(obsolete) Helpless; not performing, or not having performed, deeds or exploits; inactive.
